<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's revealed that her ex-wife Kris Jenner and daughters Kendall and Kylie Jenner didn't give her a heads up that Keeping Up With The Kardashians is ending after 20 seasons on cable network E!.</p>

<p>But in an interview with Access on Wednesday, Caitlyn Jenner shared that she thinks momager Kris would be a perfect fit for Bravo's Real Housewives Of Beverly Hills if she wants to continue on camera. </p>

<p>'Well, put it this way, Kris could handle all of those women and some others, yes,' Caitlyn, 70, told the outlet. </p>

<p>Career suggestion: Caitlyn Jenner thinks her ex Kris Jenner would be perfect for Real Housewives of Beverly Hills now that Keeping Up With The Kardashians is ending after 14 years</p>

<p>'That's kind of in her element. I think she would do really well. She would have a lot to say with all these girls. ... She would be phenomenal on that show,' the transgender reality star added.</p>

<p>On Thursday, Caitlyn told Australia's The Morning Show that she found out about the end of KUWTK on the news like everyone else.</p>

<p>'Nobody called me, I heard it through the media. Was I surprised? No,' she added. </p>

<p>She then praised her ex-wife Kris Jenner and their family for putting on a great show for 20 seasons over 14 years.</p>

<p>'That show, it's probably the greatest reality show in history. There are over 500 episodes over 14 years,' Caitlyn said.Kris could handle all of those women</p>

<p>New role? 'Kris could handle all of those women.....I think she would do really well. She would have a lot to say with all these girls. ... She would be phenomenal on that show,' Caitlyn said</p>

<p>Good job: Caitlyn also praised Kris Jenner and their family for putting on a great show, calling Keeping Up With The Kardashians 'probably the greatest reality show in history'</p>

<p>Left out of the loop: In a shocking revelation, Caitlyn, 70, told Australia's The Morning Show that she found out about the end of KUWTK on the news like everyone else</p>

<p>'The girls and Kris have have done just an amazing job with the show and keeping it going for this long. But everybody is in a different place now and I think it's time to move on. But what a run.'</p>

<p>She added that 'nothing lasts forever' and said her family was now focusing on new ventures, like cosmetics and clothing lines.   </p>

<p>'I wasn't surprised but I just am so proud of the kids for doing such a great job over the years... I don't know the inner workings of all the family, but I know all of the kids have moved on into their own areas,' she said. </p>

<p>Caitlyn was a regular part of Keeping Up with the Kardashians from its debut in 2007 until her divorce from Kris Jenner in 2015 and subsequent gender transition.</p>

<p>Speaking out: Caitlyn (left, when she was Bruce Jenner) was a regular part of KUTWK from its debut in 2007 until her divorce from Kris Jenner in 2015 and subsequent gender transition</p>

<p>The reality show was the brainchild of Kris and TV host and producer Ryan Seacrest, and followed the lives of Kris' family, which included Caitlyn - then Bruce - along with daughters Kendall and Kylie, and Kris' four children from her marriage to the late Robert Kardashian, Kourtney, Kim, Khloé and Rob.</p>

<p>At the beginning, it was Bruce who was the celebrity given his fame as a gold medalist in the decathlon at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal, Canada. </p>

<p>But in the intervening 13 years, he has been eclipsed by the phenomenal popularity of the Kardashian-Jenner siblings, who turned their family's fame into a multi-million dollar empire.</p>

<p>It was a hit: The reality show was the brainchild of Kris Jenner and TV host and producer Ryan Seacrest, and followed the lives of Kris' family, which included Caitlyn - then Bruce - along with daughters Kendall and Kylie, and Kris' four children from her marriage to the late Robert Kardashian, Kourtney, Kim, Khloé and Rob (all pictured)</p>

<p>Caitlyn starred for two seasons on the spin-off I Am Cait in 2016 and has just launched her own YouTube channel.</p>

<p>On Tuesday, Kim Kardashian shocked fans by announcing that her family's iconic reality show would be ending after 14 years on the air.</p>

<p>Keeping Up with the Kardashians, which helped make Kim and her siblings household names and launched their careers in the fashion and beauty business, will air its last season early next year.</p>

<p>There was no reason given for the decision, but E! said in a statement that it 'respects the family's decision to live their lives without our cameras'.</p>

<p>End of an era: On Tuesday, Kim Kardashian (pictured) shocked fans by announcing that her family's iconic reality show would be ending after 14 years on air </p>

<p>Kim, 39, wrote in her statement: 'To our amazing fans - It is with heavy hearts that we've made the difficult decision as a family to say goodbye to Keeping Up with the Kardashians.</p>

<p>'After what will be 14 years, 20 seasons, hundreds of episodes and numerous spin-off shows, we are beyond grateful to all of you who've watched us for all of these years – through the good times, the bad times, the happiness, the tears, and the many relationships and children.'</p>

<p>'We'll forever cherish the wonderful memories and countless people we've met along the way. Thank you to the thousands of individuals and businesses that have been a part of this experience,' she added. </p>

<p>'Most importantly, a very special thank you to Ryan Seacrest for believing in us, E! for being our partner, and our production team at Bunim/Murray, who've spent countless hours documenting our lives.</p>

<p>'Our last season will air early next year in 2021. Without Keeping Up with The Kardashians, I wouldn't be where I am today. I am so incredibly grateful to everyone who has watched and supported me and my family these past 14 incredible years.</p>

<p>'This show made us who we are and I will be forever in debt to everyone who played a role in shaping our careers and changing our lives forever. With Love and Gratitude, Kim.'</p>

<p>'So incredibly grateful': Kim, 39, wrote: 'To our amazing fans - It is with heavy hearts that we've made the difficult decision as a family to say goodbye to Keeping Up with the Kardashians'</p>
